Switch Allocation
Switch	Function
SW[7:0]	8-bit Data Input
SW[11:8]	RAM Address Input
SW12	Program Mode Select
SW13	Sensor/Input Source Select
SW14	Clock Speed Select
SW15	Demo Program Select
Details
SW[7:0]   -> Instruction/Data value
SW[11:8]  -> RAM address

SW12 = 0  -> Manual Programming Mode
SW12 = 1  -> Auto Program Loader Mode

SW13 = 0  -> Switch Input
SW13 = 1  -> Sensor Input

SW14 = 0  -> Slow Clock
SW14 = 1  -> Fast Clock

SW15 = 0  -> Demo Program 0
SW15 = 1  -> Demo Program 1
Push Button Allocation
Button	Function
BTN0	Program Write
BTN1	CPU Run
BTN2	System Reset
BTN3	Input Enter
Details
BTN0 -> Write instruction/data into RAM
BTN1 -> Start CPU execution
BTN2 -> Reset CPU, Registers, PC and Control Unit
BTN3 -> Provide user input during IN instruction
LED Allocation
LED	Function
GREEN_LED	Input Wait Indicator
RED_LED	Halt Indicator
Details
GREEN LED ON -> CPU waiting for user input
RED LED ON   -> HLT instruction executed
Seven Segment Display Allocation
Display	Function
D0 Digit 0	Output Ones
D0 Digit 1	Output Tens
D0 Digit 2	Output Hundreds
D0 Digit 3	Blank
D1 Digit 0	Program Counter (PC)
D1 Digit 1	Blank
D1 Digit 2	Current Opcode
D1 Digit 3	Current Operand

Display Format:

[Hundreds][Tens][Ones][ ]
[ PC ][ ][Opcode][Operand]
